        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued May 2 at 8:42AM CDT by NWS Memphis TN</headline>
        <description>At 842 AM CDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm near
Henderson, moving northeast at 30 mph.

HAZARD...Winds in excess of 30 mph and pea size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Jacks Creek, Lick Skillet, Sardis, Finger, Warrens Bluff, Reagan,
Rock Hill, Palestine, Roby, Montezuma, Cabo, Middle Fork, Enville,
Scotts Hill, Taylors Crossing, Shady Hill, Henderson, Chesterfield,
and Lexington.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
